        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 10 at 1:23PM CDT by NWS Houston/Galveston TX</headline>
        <description>At 123 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Webster, moving east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Southeastern Pasadena, League City, Baytown, Texas City, northeastern
Friendswood, La Porte, Dickinson, Seabrook, Webster, Kemah, South
Belt / Ellington, Clear Lake, Nassau Bay, Taylor Lake Village, El
Lago, Shoreacres, Clear Lake Shores, Morgan's Point, San Leon, and
The Johnson Space Center.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
